fixes p q v w :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "norm p / norm v = 5 / 7"
and h1 : "p = proj v w"
and h2 : "q = proj p v"
shows  "norm q / norm v = 25 / 49"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_9.informal problem: Let $p$ and $q$ be projections of vectors $w$ and $v$ respectively, with the ratio of the norm of $p$ to the norm of $v$ being $\frac{5}{7}$. Find the ratio of the norm of $q$ to the norm of $v$. The final Answer is $\frac{25}{49}$.
